(45, 'JAVA', 'Lott learned that the issue had been festering for years', 'manaor', '2019-03-19 11:57:08', 'upload/Untitled-1.jpg', '<p name=\"04e5\" id=\"04e5\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin-top: 38px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Lott learned that the issue had been festering for years, and she wanted answers. The 2,300 residents in the Fruit Belt didnâ€™t refer to the community as â€œMedical Park,â€ but Google Maps had done so since the late 2000s. Community members argued the designation was a calculated tweak in favor of gentrification, a digital rechristening that would be used to sell houses, market Airbnbs, and wrest the neighborhoodâ€™s future from the people who had made a home there for generations.</p><p name=\"3ba8\" id=\"3ba8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Lott didnâ€™t know it at the time, but the misnomer also revealed a great deal about the invisible process major tech firms use to put neighborhoods on their maps â€” and how decisions based off arcane data sets can affect y.</p><p name=\"90cc\" id=\"90cc\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Who erased the Fruit Belt? Lott demanded of officials. What the hell is Medical Park? And how did it get on this map?</p><p name=\"4c2c\" id=\"4c2c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, &quot;Times New Roman&quot;, Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-indent: -0.4em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">â€œThere is nobody in City Hall who would dare utter the phrase Medical Park anywhere near the Fruit Belt,â€ Brendan Mehaffy, the cityâ€™s chief planner, told me recently. â€œSo I really canâ€™t tell you how this happened.â€</p>', 'communities thousands of miles awa', 0, 'Published', 0),
(46, 'PHP5', 'Organize the Content Moderators', 'manoar', '2019-03-20 19:15:40', 'upload/Untitled-1.png', '<p name=\"cfe1\" id=\"cfe1\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\"><b>Some companies are worse than others</b> â€” Uberâ€™s business model&nbsp;<a href=\"https://jacobinmag.com/2018/09/uber-misclassification-gig-economy-taxi-workers-alliance\" data-href=\"https://jacobinmag.com/2018/09/uber-misclassification-gig-economy-taxi-workers-alliance\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">boils down to</a>flouting regulations and a race to the bottom for worker pay, for example â€” but direct employees of all big tech firms are slotted into a hierarchy of pay, privileges, and status, and ever larger parts of these companiesâ€™ duties are outsourced to third-party contractors. Security officers, cafeteria workers, custodial staff, shuttle drivers â€” theyâ€™re toiling for Facebook or Google or Apple, but theyâ€™re technically employees of a subcontractor. Risk, minimized; responsibility, externalized.</font></p><p name=\"a174\" id=\"a174\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">One of the fastest growing classes of subcontracted workers are the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/your-speech-their-rules-meet-the-people-who-guard-the-internet-ab58fe6b9231\" data-href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/your-speech-their-rules-meet-the-people-who-guard-the-internet-ab58fe6b9231\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">content moderators</a>&nbsp;tasked with tending to what has too often become an unwieldy spigot of porn, child abuse, and, as tragically was&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/03/18/inside-youtubes-struggles-shut-down-video-new-zealand-shooting-humans-who-outsmarted-its-systems/\" data-href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/03/18/inside-youtubes-struggles-shut-down-video-new-zealand-shooting-humans-who-outsmarted-its-systems/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">the case</a><a href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/eve7w7/documents-show-how-facebook-moderates-terrorism-on-livestreams\" data-href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/eve7w7/documents-show-how-facebook-moderates-terrorism-on-livestreams\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">&nbsp;last week</a>, a live-streamed mass shooting.</font></p><blockquote name=\"8bec\" id=\"8bec\" class=\"graf graf--pullquote graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 55px; margin-bottom: 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); border: none; padding: 0px 0px 0px 50px; --x-height-multiplier:0.342; --baseline-multiplier:0.22; font-style: italic; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.48; letter-spacing: -0.012em; text-indent: -0.32em;\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">â€œFacebook as a whole respects the right of our partner employees to organize.â€</font></blockquote><p name=\"6caf\" id=\"6caf\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--pullquote\" style=\"margin-top: 54px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">Content moderators â€œneed something much more fundamental than a campaign to join a traditional American labor union,â€ says Eric Murphy, a security officer on Facebookâ€™s main campus. Murphy, like thousands of his fellow subcontracted tech workers in the United States, recently unionized (the security guards&nbsp;<a href=\"https://gizmodo.com/after-five-years-of-fighting-google-and-facebook-secur-1828304237\" data-href=\"https://gizmodo.com/after-five-years-of-fighting-google-and-facebook-secur-1828304237\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">joined the Service Employees International Union</a>, or SEIU), but the growing army of moderators â€” around&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-02-25/facebook-grappling-with-employee-anger-over-moderator-conditions\" data-href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-02-25/facebook-grappling-with-employee-anger-over-moderator-conditions\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">15,000 for Facebook alone</a> â€” has yet to join that wave. Theyâ€™re the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/my-awful-life-as-the-internets-janitor\" data-href=\"https://www.gq.com/story/my-awful-life-as-the-internets-janitor\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">janitors of the internet</a>, low-paid workers who scrub these platforms to make them look a bit more like the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/whatsapp-wont-solve-the-facebook-problems-you-worry-about-24e21e8fdcb4\" data-href=\"https://onezero.medium.com/whatsapp-wont-solve-the-facebook-problems-you-worry-about-24e21e8fdcb4\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">immaculate visions</a>&nbsp;conjured by their executives.</font></p><p name=\"d229\" id=\"d229\" class=\"graf graf--p graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; text-indent: -0.4em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">â€œMaybe if Mark Zuckerberg had to do the job for a week, he would have some ideas about how to fix it,â€ Murphy notes.</font></p><p name=\"07f7\" id=\"07f7\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\">Many subcontracted workers who labor on or near tech campuses see the industryâ€™s immense wealth up close every day, and they view the widespread practice of subcontracting as a way to keep them from accessing it. As&nbsp;<a href=\"https://nplusonemag.com/issue-31/politics/code-red/\" data-href=\"https://nplusonemag.com/issue-31/politics/code-red/\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">Murphy told me</a>&nbsp;last year, â€œMy coworkers and I dream about going direct with Facebook: Thatâ€™s where the money is, thatâ€™s where the power is, and this artifice of subcontracting is just a scheme to hold down our wages and prevent us from getting a whack at the Facebook piÃ±ata.â€</font></p><p name=\"726d\" id=\"726d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-top: 29px; margin-bottom: 0px; --x-height-multiplier:0.375; --baseline-multiplier:0.17; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><font face=\"comic sans ms\"><b>Content moderators,</b> by contrast, operate in relative isolation, hidden away from gleaming Silicon Valley campuses, their existence downplayed by executives who&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/27/18242724/facebook-moderation-ai-artificial-intelligence-platforms\" data-href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2019/2/27/18242724/facebook-moderation-ai-artificial-intelligence-platforms\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">tout A.I.â€™s role in moderation</a>, even as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/xwk9zd/how-facebook-content-moderation-works\" data-href=\"https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/xwk9zd/how-facebook-content-moderation-works\" class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: inherit; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: url(&quot;data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg preserveAspectRatio=&quot;none&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1 1&quot; xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot;><line x1=&quot;0&quot; y1=&quot;0&quot; x2=&quot;1&quot; y2=&quot;1&quot; stroke=&quot;currentColor&quot; /></svg>&quot;); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\">human beings do much</a>of the heavy lifting.</font></p>', 'the,content,creator', 0, 'Published', 52);
